# Go Conventions

## Package Layout

- `cmd/yaitracker/` -- thin CLI entrypoint (Cobra)
- `internal/` -- all private application code (compiler-enforced)
- Root package -- embedded assets only (embed.go)

## Naming

- Exported: `PascalCase`. Unexported: `camelCase`
- JSON tags: `snake_case` (`json:"project_id"`)
- Acronyms: `ID`, `URL`, `HTTP` (all caps), not `Id`, `Url`

## Error Handling

- Wrap at every boundary: `fmt.Errorf("create project: %w", err)`
- Sentinel errors per package: `var ErrNotFound = errors.New("not found")`
- Compare with `errors.Is`/`errors.As`, never `==`
- Never discard errors from I/O with `_`

## Documentation

- Every exported type and function: `// Name does X.`
- Package comment in one file per package: `// Package store provides ...`

## Dependencies

- No new deps without justification. Prefer stdlib.
- Current direct deps: chi, goose, cobra, x/crypto, modernc/sqlite, mcp-go

## SQL

- Parameterized queries only (`?` placeholders)
- Use `store.writeTx` for all mutations
- Goose for migrations in `migrations/`

## Context

- `context.Context` as first parameter on all I/O functions
- Pass `r.Context()` from HTTP handlers into store methods
